File: Eskom downgraded load-shedding from stage 2 to stage 1. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says it will suspend load-shedding at 12pm on Sunday. This after it announced Stage 1 load-shedding from 7am on Sunday. Eskom says Koeberg Unit 1 has been safely synchronised onto the grid, and that's helping to ease the scale of load-shedding. READ: Load-shedding for the weekend Eskom says it's making progress in restoring emergency reserves to meet demand for the coming week. People are urged to continue using electricity sparingly.